50|$|On December 28, 2016, U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry {{strongly}} criticized Israel and its <b>settlement</b> <b>policies</b> in a speech. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu strongly {{criticized the}} UN Resolution and Kerry's speech. On January 6, 2017, the Israeli government withdrew its annual dues from the organization, which totaled $6 million in United States dollars. On January 5, 2017, the United States House of Representatives voted 342-80 {{to condemn the}} UN Resolution.|$|R
